<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `organization` Reference field on the `x_[scope]_case_party`
    custom table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim) for x_[scope]_case_party:

        Field         Type                          Constraints
        organization  Reference -> core_company     Conditional: required if
                                                    party_type = Organization

    Per AAP Section 0.4.3 (Design Pattern Applications):
        "Polymorphic association via single-table choice + UI Policy -
         case_party collapses ArkCase's two association tables
         (acm_person_assoc, acm_person_org_assoc) into one ServiceNow table
         with a Choice discriminator (party_type) and a UI Policy that
         conditionally shows person (reference -> sys_user) or organization
         (reference -> core_company)."

    THIS FIELD IS THE ORGANIZATION HALF OF THE POLYMORPHIC PARTY MODEL.
    Together with its sibling `person` field
    (../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_person.xml -> Reference -> sys_user),
    `organization` represents one of two mutually exclusive sub-shapes of a
    party row, with the choice between them driven by the `party_type`
    discriminator (../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_party_type.xml). When
    party_type = Organization, this `organization` reference is required and
    visible while `person` is hidden and ignored. When party_type = Person,
    this `organization` reference is hidden and ignored while `person` is
    required and visible. The conditional show/hide and conditional
    mandatoriness are NOT enforced at the dictionary level here - they are
    enforced by the UI Policy at
    ../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml. THIS dictionary
    entry simply DECLARES that the column exists, that it is a Reference to
    core_company, and that the dictionary-level mandatory flag is FALSE so
    the polymorphism remains correct (Person-typed rows must be allowed to
    save with `organization` empty).

    Critical behaviors that depend on this field (AAP Sections 0.4.3, 0.4.4,
    0.5.7, 0.7.4):

      1. CONDITIONAL VISIBILITY VIA UI POLICY
         (../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml)
         Per AAP Section 0.1.2 verbatim: "The case_party polymorphic
         conditional fields (person shown when party_type = Person;
         organization shown when party_type = Organization) are implemented
         via UI Policies on the form." The UI Policy at the path above runs
         on the case_party form and:
           * When party_type = Organization: sets organization.visible = true,
                                             organization.mandatory = true,
                                             person.visible = false,
                                             person.mandatory = false
           * When party_type = Person:       sets organization.visible = false,
                                             organization.mandatory = false,
                                             person.visible = true,
                                             person.mandatory = true
         The UI Policy READS this dictionary entry's element name
         (`organization`) to know which form field to manipulate. Without
         THIS dictionary entry, the UI Policy could not find a column named
         `organization` to bind its actions against, and the conditional
         visibility would silently fail to apply. Note that the UI Policy
         operates at the FORM layer only - server-side GlideRecord.insert()
         / Table API POST do NOT run UI Policies, which is why
         mandatory=false at the dictionary level and the "Conditional:
         required if party_type=Organization" semantics are enforced by
         THIS particular UI Policy combined with the platform's form
         rendering, NOT by a hard mandatory=true flag that would break
         Person-typed rows.

      2. ORGANIZATION HALF OF THE POLYMORPHISM-COLLAPSE PATTERN
         (../tables/x_[scope]_case_party.xml,
          ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_party_type.xml,
          ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_person.xml)
         AAP Section 0.4.3's "Polymorphic association via single-table
         choice + UI Policy" pattern collapses ArkCase's TWO source JPA
         entities (PersonAssociation -> acm_person_assoc and
         PersonOrganizationAssociation -> acm_person_org_assoc) into the
         SINGLE ServiceNow table x_[scope]_case_party, where:
           * party_type carries the discriminator (Person | Organization)
           * person carries the sys_user pointer when party_type = Person
             (replacing PersonAssociation.person @ManyToOne(Person) and
             PersonOrganizationAssociation.person @ManyToOne(Person))
           * THIS `organization` field carries the core_company pointer
             when party_type = Organization (replacing
             PersonOrganizationAssociation.organization
             @ManyToOne(Organization))
         The collapse is semantically lossless within the POC scope (AAP
         Section 0.3.1) because:
           * The POC's only "thing parties attach to" is the case (parent
             linkage handled by ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_case.xml),
             not the multi-target attach-anywhere pattern of
             PersonAssociation.parentId/parentType in ArkCase.
           * The PersonOrganizationAssociation pattern (a Person tied to an
             Organization, with both references on the same row) is OUT OF
             SCOPE per AAP Section 0.3.2's enumerated POC feature set, which
             only requires attaching a Person OR an Organization (mutually
             exclusive) to a case. The Organization-typed party rows on
             x_[scope]_case_party therefore preserve only the Organization
             reference half of PersonOrganizationAssociation, dropping the
             bundled Person reference, and any "primary contact / default
             organization / association type" metadata from the source
             entity which is irrelevant to the POC scope.
         Note that AAP Section 0.5.7's "Conditional: required if
         party_type = Organization" qualifier is the canonical contract
         for this field's mandatoriness - it is REQUIRED, but only in
         the context of Organization-typed rows. The dictionary's hard
         mandatory=false ensures that Person-typed rows can save with
         this field empty; the UI Policy reinstates a conditional
         mandatory=true at the form layer when the chosen party_type
         is Organization.

      3. AGENT/MANAGER FORM EDITING WITH OOB core_company PICKER
         (parent table ../tables/x_[scope]_case_party.xml automatic form
          layout per AAP Section 0.4.4 "Internal user UI" requirements)
         AAP Section 0.4.4 declares: "the internal user UI is provided by
         ServiceNow's automatic native list and form views for the three
         custom tables." When a case_manager or case_agent opens a
         case_party form with party_type = Organization, the auto-rendered
         picker for THIS field surfaces ALL active core_company records
         via the platform's standard reference-field combobox/typeahead.
         The user can search the core_company directory by name (the OOB
         display column) to find the correct organization to associate
         with the case. Once selected, the platform persists the chosen
         company's 32-character sys_id in this column. The picker
         auto-dereferences the company's display column (core_company.name)
         for human-readable rendering on the form, in the case_party list
         view, and in the case form's Related List of parties. This
         deferred dereference is what allows the seed data and the demo
         cases to reference companies by stable human-readable name
         rather than by hard-coded sys_id, per AAP Section 0.7.2's
         "no-hardcoded-sys_id constraint."

      4. ACL "ASSIGNED ONLY" CASCADE FOR CASE_AGENT
         (../acl/x_[scope]_case_party_*.xml)
         Per AAP Section 0.5.6: case_agent has "Assigned only" CRUD
         access. For parties, "Assigned only" propagates THROUGH the
         parent `case` reference (declared in
         ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_case.xml), NOT through THIS
         `organization` field. A case_agent does NOT gain or lose access
         to a party row based on whether this `organization` field
         happens to point at any particular core_company - access is
         determined solely by the parent case's assigned_agent /
         assigned_group columns. This means a case_agent who works for a
         particular core_company (e.g., as the corp's internal liaison)
         does NOT thereby gain edit access to OTHER parties on cases
         that simply HAPPEN to reference the same core_company unless
         they are also the case's assigned_agent or in the case's
         assigned_group. This separation is intentional: the AAP's
         authorization model explicitly distinguishes "owner"
         (assigned_agent) from "associated" (party.organization), and
         only the former confers operational access. The
         party.organization column thus carries
         RECORD-OF-ASSOCIATION semantics, not RECORD-OF-OWNERSHIP
         semantics - a critical distinction inherited from the source
         model where ArkCase's PersonOrganizationAssociation tracked
         organization associations independently of the case assignee.

      5. PORTAL-LOOKUP FIELD WHITELIST EXCLUSION
         (../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_status_lookup.xml)
         Per AAP Section 0.7.4: "the lookup page returns ONLY status,
         subject, opened_date - no internal fields exposed." Party data
         (including the `person` and `organization` references) is NOT
         exposed by the portal status-lookup endpoint. An anonymous
         external requester querying their case status by number sees
         only the three whitelisted top-level case fields and learns
         nothing about who else is associated to the case (whether by
         name, role, or organizational affiliation). This is a
         strict-by-default privacy posture aligned with AAP Section
         0.3.2's no-PII-exposure stance. THIS dictionary entry therefore
         deliberately does NOT participate in any portal-facing schema;
         the field is INTERNAL-ONLY by construction.

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonOrganizationAssociation.java
        lines 86-88:
            @ManyToOne(cascade = { CascadeType.REFRESH, CascadeType.DETACH,
                CascadeType.PERSIST }, optional = false)
            @JoinColumn(name = "cm_organization_id", nullable = false)
            private Organization organization;
        ArkCase's PersonOrganizationAssociation entity (mapped to
        acm_person_org_assoc, the SECOND of the two source association
        tables that this ServiceNow target collapses into one) carried a
        NOT-NULL @ManyToOne relationship to the Organization domain
        entity (a separate @Entity-mapped JPA class living in the
        acm-person-plugin alongside Person, with its own dedicated table
        acm_organization and a sub-schema covering organization name,
        organization type, addresses, identifications, contact-method
        rollups, default-organization flag, and parent-child organization
        hierarchy). The @JoinColumn was named cm_organization_id and was
        DECLARED NOT NULL (`nullable = false`), with a cascade set
        covering REFRESH, DETACH, and PERSIST (intentionally narrower
        than PersonOrganizationAssociation.person's cascade set, which
        included MERGE - reflecting that an Organization edit detected
        through a PersonOrganizationAssociation was less likely to be
        the user's intent than a Person edit was). The `optional = false`
        plus the @JoinColumn `nullable = false` together produced a hard
        constraint at both the JPA validation layer and the MySQL DDL
        layer that no acm_person_org_assoc row could ever exist with a
        NULL cm_organization_id - which makes sense in the context of
        ArkCase, since the entire point of an acm_person_org_assoc row
        was to record a Person-Organization linkage and a row with no
        Organization side would have been semantically meaningless.

        The ServiceNow target ALTERS this contract in two ways (AAP
        Sections 0.1.2, 0.4.3, 0.5.7):
          * The Organization domain entity is REPLACED by the OOB
            core_company table. ArkCase's separate Organization directory
            (mapped to acm_organization) is OUT OF SCOPE per AAP Section
            0.3.2's enumerated POC feature set - the POC has no
            requirement for a directory of "organizations the corporation
            knows about" beyond ServiceNow's standard core_company
            roster, which already covers customer companies, vendor
            companies, and partner companies in the platform's standard
            CMDB-adjacent organizational graph and could be extended
            with synthetic core_company records to represent
            Complainant-side organizations or Respondent-side
            organizations as needed. Replacing Organization with
            core_company gains: referential integrity (the core_company
            picker enforces existing-row selection); single source of
            truth (the same table backing CMDB company affiliations,
            customer support catalog, and other ServiceNow surfaces);
            and zero dependency on a separate organization-directory
            plugin. The trade-off is the loss of ArkCase's richer
            Organization sub-schema (multiple addresses, multiple
            identifiers, default-organization marker, parent/child org
            hierarchy) which is irrelevant to the POC's case-association
            feature set. Note that core_company is the OOB ServiceNow
            table name (lowercase, with a "core_" prefix that is part of
            the OOB schema convention for foundational organizational
            tables); it is NOT cmn_company (the older platform name from
            pre-Eureka era), NOT customer_account (a CSM-specific
            table), and NOT any other variant. AAP Section 0.5.7
            specifies this exact target table by name.
          * The NOT NULL constraint is REPLACED by a CONDITIONAL
            mandatory constraint enforced by UI Policy. ArkCase's
            cm_organization_id was unconditionally NOT NULL because
            PersonOrganizationAssociation rows ALWAYS represented a
            person-to-organization association (the Organization side
            was always present by definition; the entity simply could
            not exist without it). In the ServiceNow target,
            x_[scope]_case_party collapses two source tables into one
            polymorphic table; for Person-typed rows, this `organization`
            column MUST be empty (the polymorphism semantics demand it),
            which is incompatible with a hard NOT NULL constraint. The
            CONDITIONAL mandatoriness (required only when party_type =
            Organization) is the ServiceNow-idiomatic equivalent.

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonAssociation.java
        is the SIBLING JPA entity for person-only associations to ArkCase
        parents (mapped to acm_person_assoc). It contributes NO direct
        organization-pointing data to the polymorphism collapse - per
        ArkCase's source model, only PersonOrganizationAssociation
        carried an Organization reference, while PersonAssociation
        carried only a Person reference. In the ServiceNow target, the
        polymorphism collapse means BOTH source-table shapes share the
        single x_[scope]_case_party schema:
          * Person-typed rows (party_type = Person) populate the
            `person` field but leave THIS `organization` field empty -
            this case represents the "PersonAssociation pattern" in
            shape (a person attached directly to a case).
          * Organization-typed rows (party_type = Organization)
            populate THIS `organization` field but leave `person`
            empty - this case represents the "PersonOrganizationAssociation
            pattern" in shape (an organization attached to a case),
            with the bundled Person reference dropped per AAP Section
            0.3.2's enumerated POC feature set.
        The discrimination between person-type associations and
        organization-type associations is now carried by the
        `party_type` Choice field
        (../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_party_type.xml), not by
        separate physical tables. THIS dictionary entry is therefore
        relevant only to Organization-typed rows; Person-typed rows
        always have this column NULL.

      - The field name is `organization` (lowercase, 12 chars, no prefix;
        NOT `org`, NOT `org_ref`, NOT `org_id`, NOT `company`, NOT
        `org_company`) per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. This single
        unqualified word was deliberately chosen by the AAP for two
        reasons:
          * It mirrors the parallel ArkCase JPA field name `organization`
            (PersonOrganizationAssociation.java line 88), preserving
            naming familiarity for any future developer migrating from
            the source codebase.
          * It complements the sibling `person` field name on the same
            table (also a single unqualified word; the same naming
            pattern is used by AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim for BOTH
            polymorphism halves), making the polymorphism-collapse
            pattern visually obvious in the field list.
        The dictionary-level column_label "Organization" (capitalized,
        title-case) is consistent with the AAP-implied human-readable
        label set across the data model (e.g., "Subject", "Type",
        "Status", "Priority", "Person" - all single capitalized words).

      - ArkCase's Organization entity used a MySQL InnoDB BIGINT primary
        key with no explicit length cap; the @JoinColumn cm_organization_id
        stored that bigint. The ServiceNow target uses the standard
        32-character Reference-field width to store the sys_id of the
        chosen core_company row; the platform's auto-generated form
        picker, list view, and report builder all dereference to the
        company's display column (core_company.name) for human-readable
        display via the OOB core_company dictionary's display=true
        configuration.

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to
        `x_[scope]_case_party` within the scoped application, and
        `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>` bind THIS dictionary record to
        the same scope by `source` attribute lookup. The `<reference>`
        element resolves to OOB `core_company` by table name (NOT by
        sys_id), preserving zero-hardcoded-sys_id compliance. NO
        global-scope writes - the OOB `core_company` table is
        REFERENCED but never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>`,
        `<sys_package>`, and `<reference>` text-node values resolve by
        scope source name and table name respectively, not by literal
        sys_id. The `<sys_id>` text-node value is THIS record's own
        deterministic primary key (MD5 of the canonical field
        identifier `x_[scope]_case_party.organization` =
        1fa3f30c65afbf042f32440bf955199f) and is NOT a reference to any
        other record. Per AAP Section 0.7.2 this scheme guarantees that
        a fresh PDI re-import of the Update Set produces byte-identical
        sys_id values, which is necessary for round-trip-verify
        (../scripts/round_trip_verify.md) zero-error preview.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP
        convention; the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App
        Engine Studio creation time and substitutes it into every
        occurrence at export.
      - mandatory=false at the dictionary level (CRITICAL: AAP Section
        0.5.7's "Conditional: required if party_type = Organization" is
        a POLYMORPHISM-LEVEL constraint enforced by the UI Policy at
        ../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml, NOT a
        FIELD-LEVEL constraint enforced by the dictionary). Setting
        this to true would prevent Person-typed party rows from being
        saved (since they have no organization), which DIRECTLY
        contradicts the polymorphism collapse pattern (AAP Section
        0.4.3) and the AAP Section 0.5.7 enumerated party_type list
        (Person, Organization, both supported on the same table). The
        UI Policy reinstates conditional mandatoriness at the form
        layer when party_type = Organization, which is the correct
        ServiceNow-idiomatic enforcement point for choice-driven field
        requiredness.
      - read_only=false: case_manager and case_agent both edit this
        field directly when associating an organization party to a
        case. The auto-generated New Party form on the case's Related
        List pre-populates the parent `case` reference, then surfaces
        the party_type picker; once Organization is selected, the UI
        Policy reveals THIS organization field for editing.
      - default_value (empty): no automatic organization assignment.
        The AAP Section 0.5.7 specification is "Conditional: required
        if party_type = Organization" - which inherently means there
        is no sensible platform-wide default. The user explicitly
        chooses the organization at form-fill time.
      - audit=false: per AAP Section 0.3.1 minimal-change clause and
        consistent with the sibling Reference / DateTime / Choice /
        String fields in this same dictionary set. The sys_history_set
        / sys_audit infrastructure on demand still captures party-row
        audit events at the row level via the platform's standard
        sys_* audit columns; per-field audit on `organization` would
        inflate sys_audit storage with low-value entries (a party
        row's organization rarely changes after initial assignment).
      - max_length=32: the standard ServiceNow Reference-field width.
        The dictionary stores the 32-character lowercase-hex sys_id of
        the referenced core_company row as the actual column value;
        the platform's auto-generated form picker, list view, and
        report builder all dereference to the company's display column
        for human-readable display via the OOB core_company
        dictionary's display=true column.
      - choice=0: this is a Reference field, NOT a Choice field. The
        sibling sys_choice_* records under ../choices/ apply only to
        the `type`, `status`, `priority`, `pending_reason`,
        `case_task.type`, `case_task.status`, and `case_party.party_type`
        columns - none are needed here.
      - choice_field, choice_table empty: same reason as choice=0
        above.
      - reference=core_company: OOB ServiceNow company directory
        table. AAP Section 0.5.7 specifies this exact target table by
        name (NOT `cmn_company` - the pre-Eureka platform name; NOT
        `customer_account` - a CSM-specific table; NOT `task`; NOT any
        other variant). The platform resolves the table-name
        cross-reference at Update Set import time by querying
        sys_db_object.name; core_company is always present on every
        PDI as part of the OOB schema, so no explicit
        dependency-ordering is needed (in contrast to
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_case.xml whose
        `<reference>x_[scope]_case</reference>` requires
        ../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml to be loaded first).
      - reference_cascade_rule (empty): default platform behavior,
        which is "do nothing on referenced-record deletion." If a
        core_company is deleted (a rare administrative operation
        typically gated by global ACLs and CMDB-relationship policies),
        party rows retain the orphaned reference; this is acceptable
        for the POC since core_company deletion is a global-admin-level
        operation and is rare in practice. The sibling
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_person.xml uses the same
        empty cascade rule for the same reason (both point at OOB
        directory tables that are rarely deleted). AAP does not
        specify a cascade rule for this column.
      - reference_qual, reference_qual_condition (empty): no filter on
        which core_company records may be selected. ANY core_company
        is eligible at the picker level. AAP Section 0.5.7 does not
        require filtering by company type, vendor flag, customer flag,
        or any other criterion - a party may be ANY company,
        including companies that exist purely in the CMDB for
        non-case-related purposes (e.g., a vendor company whose
        services were the subject of a complaint). A future
        enhancement could add a dynamic ref qual such as
        `vendor=true^ORcustomer=true` or a more sophisticated scoping
        rule, but that is not in scope per AAP Section 0.3.1's
        MINIMAL CHANGE CLAUSE.
      - use_reference_qualifier=simple: standard ServiceNow setting
        when no advanced (scripted) reference qualifier is in use.
      - dynamic_ref_qual (empty): no dynamic reference qualifier - see
        reference_qual rationale above.
      - reference_floor, reference_key, reference_type (empty):
        standard defaults for a basic table-to-table reference; no
        advanced reference semantics (typeahead override, reference
        floor table, document reference, etc.) are needed here.
      - element_reference=false: this is a TABLE reference, not an
        ELEMENT reference (which would point at a specific dictionary
        column on another table). AAP specifies a row-level reference
        target.
      - table_reference=false: this is NOT a "Document ID" / "Table"
        polymorphic reference (which is what `glide_var` style fields
        on the OOB task table use to reference any-table-any-row). It
        is a fixed-target reference to core_company only. Note that
        the polymorphism in case_party operates at a HIGHER level -
        via the party_type Choice plus the sibling person/organization
        Reference fields - not via a table-level polymorphic
        reference like Document ID would provide.
      - text_index=false: Reference fields are not full-text-indexed.
        Searches by company are performed via GlideRecord
        addJoinQuery against core_company on its sys_id column;
        full-text indexing of the 32-char sys_id has no value.
      - unique=false: a single company may correctly be a party on
        multiple cases (e.g., a known vendor that appears as
        respondent on many complaint cases). Uniqueness on this
        column would be semantically wrong and would prevent the seed
        data from creating multiple party rows pointing at the same
        demo company. AAP Section 0.7.4 minimum demo-data thresholds
        explicitly require "at least one Person and one Organization
        party per demo case" with no constraint that Organization
        rows must reference DIFFERENT companies across cases - in
        fact, the seed plan reuses synthetic companies across multiple
        demo cases for compactness.
      - virtual=false: this is a stored column, not a calculated /
        virtual derivation. The actual sys_id of the chosen
        core_company row is persisted on every party record.
      - spell_check=false: Reference fields hold a 32-char sys_id and
        the platform renders the dereferenced display value at view
        time; spell-check is meaningless for the persisted value and
        would be misapplied to the dereferenced organization-name
        display.
      - No PII: the field stores a 32-char sys_id pointer to a company
        record; the company record itself stores categorical
        organizational identity (synthetic company name only) per AAP
        Section 0.7.2 ("synthetic only"). The seed data may create
        synthetic core_company rows (e.g., "Demo Vendor Inc",
        "Sample Respondent Corp") referenced by name; no real
        company names, real addresses, or PII derived from the
        source ArkCase database are placed in this column at any
        point in the build.

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER:
          * ../tables/x_[scope]_case_party.xml (parent table; `<name>`
            here references the scoped party table by name; the
            platform requires the table to exist before its
            dictionary entries can be created)
          * core_company (OOB; always present on every PDI; never
            modified by this Update Set per AAP Section 0.3.2)
      - This record MUST load BEFORE the consumers that read or write
        the `organization` column on x_[scope]_case_party:
          * ../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
            (the polymorphism UI Policy that toggles visibility/
            mandatoriness of THIS field based on party_type; the
            policy's actions reference the column by element name
            `organization`, which requires this dictionary entry to
            exist so the platform's UI Policy editor can resolve the
            reference at design time AND at form-render time)
          * ../acl/x_[scope]_case_party_*.xml (table-level ACLs on
            the case_party table; while THIS field is not directly
            named in any ACL condition, the table-level ACLs read
            ALL fields on the row and therefore implicitly cover the
            `organization` field's read/write authorization within
            the case_agent "Assigned only" condition that dot-walks
            current.case.assigned_agent and current.case.assigned_group)
          * ../seed-data/parties/x_[scope]_case_party_demo_*.xml
            (synthetic demo parties that populate THIS field for
            party_type = Organization rows by lookup of the demo
            company's name attribute via the seed_demo_data.js
            script - never via hard-coded sys_id, per AAP Section
            0.7.2 the no-hardcoded-sys_id constraint applies to
            flows, ACL conditions, scripts, seed data, UI Policies,
            UI Actions, Business Rules, and client scripts; AAP
            Section 0.7.4 minimum demo-data thresholds explicitly
            require "at least one Person and one Organization party
            per demo case to exercise the polymorphic UI policy" -
            which mandates that the demo seed contains rows with
            party_type = Organization and a populated organization
            reference)
          * ../scripts/seed_demo_data.js (the idempotent seed script
            that creates the demo party rows; for each
            Organization-typed demo party it performs:
                var orgGr = new GlideRecord('core_company');
                orgGr.addQuery('name', '<demo-company-name>');
                orgGr.query();
                if (orgGr.next()) { partyGr.organization = orgGr.sys_id; }
            to resolve the company sys_id at seed time, never via
            hard-coded literals)
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
    <sys_dictionary action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <array>false</array>
        <attributes/>
        <audit>false</audit>
        <calculation/>
        <choice>0</choice>
        <choice_field/>
